Syntax:
Create table <table name> (<col1> <datatype>(<size>),<col2> <datatype><size>));
2. Modifying the structure of tables.
a) Add new columns
Syntax:
Alter table <tablename> add(<new col><datatype(size),<new col>datatype(size));
b) Dropping a column from a table.
Syntax:
Alter table <tablename> drop column <col>;
Ex:alter table emp drop column sal;
3. Modifying existing columns.
Syntax:
Alter table <tablename> modify(<col><newdatatype>(<newsize>));
4. Renaming the tables
Syntax:
Rename <oldtable> to <new table>;
5. Truncating the tables.
Syntax:
Truncate table <tablename>;
Ex:trunc table emp1;
6. Destroying tables.
Syntax:
Drop table <tablename>;
